HEADWORD: Quarry-faced
<hw>Quar"ry-faced`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Stone
Masonry)</fld> <def>Having a face left as it comes from the quarry and
not smoothed with the chisel or point; -- said of stones.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

